title: For Sale:  7.65 French, 7.65 MAS, 7.65×20, 7.65Long - New Old Stock
postcontent:
I have several hundred rounds of this ammo - all new old stock.  It's the steel case stuff from the WW2 era, with varying head stamps, and has been stored in a cool, dry location, in a sealed ammo can since the early 60's, with a bag of rice dessicant.  

10 out of 10 random rounds fired when tested.  Prior to gaining day access to an appropriate firearm, I disassembled 10 random rounds and tested the components.  All functioned as expected.  With 20 out of 20 proving viable, I've got to assume all, or a significant percentage, are viable.

I know this stuff is rare to the point of being insanely so, with people cutting down and resizing brass from other ammo just to get something close - and when you can find some "factory" stuff that they've done that with, they're asking $80, or more, for 50 rounds.  

$30 per bag of 50 rounds.

If you have had dealings with any of these people please email me at REDACTED (my real email address). I will add you to the case. Also, please contact your local Postal Inspector to open a mail fraud complaint (conspiracy to commit is a crime, too, so you need not have actually sent payment) and possibly your local FBI office. Paula Cruz is a real person in Long Island, NY (ATF has spoken with her) but she has a good "innocent" sob story so they likely will not be able to do much unless more evidence flows in. I believe Victor Antoine is a real person also, and is part of this conspiracy.

I know of at least two true victims who are out respectively over $700 for guns that didn't even exist.

Ads by these scammers have been flagged many, many times at Armslist and yet they continue. PROTECT yourself! Check all listings by the user. If they are listing items from multiple states it's a scam! Only send payment to a licensed dealer and contact the dealer first to make sure that this person is a known customer!

Screw these scammers! They are only making it harder for us gun owners (yes, gun enthusiasts and gun "lovers" to continue our tradition/sport/livelihood in these troubled times).

ARMSLIST IS DOING NOTHING TO STOP THESE SCAMS! IP ADDRESSES CAN BE TRACKED AND FLAGGED!
